  "all::Jan2020_P2HR__Q16__p16-17__m08__Probability-Diagrams-Venn-and-Tree-Diagrams": {
    "status": "missing",
    "source": "**Topic check:** Probability Diagrams - Venn & Tree Diagrams. The tag is correct.\n\n**Solution**\n\nFor Cody:\n\n\\[\nP(A\\text{ odd})=\\frac{7}{10},\\qquad P(A\\text{ even})=\\frac{3}{10}\n\\]\n\n\\[\nP(B\\text{ odd})=\\frac{7}{12},\\qquad P(B\\text{ even})=\\frac{5}{12}\n\\]\n\nAn odd total comes from odd + even or even + odd:\n\n\\[\n\\frac{7}{10}\\times\\frac{5}{12}+\\frac{3}{10}\\times\\frac{7}{12}\n=\\frac{7}{15}\n\\]\n\nCody takes two even counters with probability\n\n\\[\n\\frac{3}{10}\\times\\frac{5}{12}=\\frac18\n\\]\n\nGiven Cody and Harriet both take two even counters:\n\n\\[\n\\frac18\\times P(H\\text{ even})=\\frac{3}{100}\n\\]\n\n\\[\nP(H\\text{ even})=\\frac{6}{25}\n\\]\n\nSo Harriet's bag must have at least \\(25\\) counters.\n\n**Answers:** \\(\\frac{7}{15}\\), and \\(25\\).",
    "updated": "2026-05-06T18:49:24",
    "checked_by": ""
  },
  "expertise::Jan2020_P2HR__Q21__p22-22__m07__Algebraic-Roots-and-Indices": {
    "status": "checked",
    "source": "**Topic check:** Correct.\n\n**Method**\n\n(a)\n\n\\[\n\\frac{10x^2+23x+12}{4x^2-9}\n=\\frac{(5x+4)(2x+3)}{(2x-3)(2x+3)}\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=\\frac{5x+4}{2x-3}\n\\]\n\n(b)\n\n\\[\n2^{2y}\\times 2^{3y+2}=2^{5y+2}\n\\]\n\nAlso,\n\n\\[\n\\frac{8^{5y}}{4^n}\n=\\frac{(2^3)^{5y}}{(2^2)^n}\n=2^{15y-2n}\n\\]\n\nEquate powers:\n\n\\[\n5y+2=15y-2n\n\\]\n\n\\[\n2n=10y-2\n\\]\n\n\\[\nn=5y-1\n\\]\n\n**Answer:** (a) \\(\\dfrac{5x+4}{2x-3}\\), (b) \\(n=5y-1\\)",
    "updated": "2026-05-05",
    "checked_by": "Dr Eslam Ahmed + Codex"
  },
  "expertise::Jan2020_P2HR__Q23__p23-23__m03__Completing-the-Square": {
    "status": "checked",
    "source": "**Topic check:** Correct.\n\n**Method**\n\n\\[\n7-12x-2x^2=-2x^2-12x+7\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=-2(x^2+6x)+7\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=-2\\left((x+3)^2-9\\right)+7\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=-2(x+3)^2+18+7\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=25-2(x+3)^2\n\\]\n\n**Answer:** \\(25-2(x+3)^2\\)",
    "updated": "2026-05-05",
    "checked_by": "Dr Eslam Ahmed + Codex"
  },
  "expertise::Jan2020_P2HR__Q25__p25-25__m03__Algebraic-Proof": {
    "status": "checked",
    "source": "**Topic check:** Corrected from Right-Angled Triangles to Algebraic Proof.\n\n**Method**\n\nSince \\(N\\) is a multiple of 5, let\n\n\\[\nN=5k\n\\]\n\nwhere \\(k\\) is an integer.\n\nGiven\n\n\\[\nA=N+1,\\qquad B=N-1\n\\]\n\nSo\n\n\\[\nA^2-B^2=(N+1)^2-(N-1)^2\n\\]\n\nExpand:\n\n\\[\n(N+1)^2=N^2+2N+1\n\\]\n\n\\[\n(N-1)^2=N^2-2N+1\n\\]\n\nTherefore\n\n\\[\nA^2-B^2=(N^2+2N+1)-(N^2-2N+1)\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=4N\n\\]\n\nSubstitute \\(N=5k\\):\n\n\\[\n4N=4(5k)=20k\n\\]\n\nSince \\(k\\) is an integer, \\(20k\\) is a multiple of 20.\n\n**Answer:** \\(A^2-B^2\\) is always a multiple of \\(20\\).",
    "updated": "2026-05-05",
    "checked_by": "Dr Eslam Ahmed + Codex"
  },
