    "status": "checked",
    "source": "**Topic check:** Correct.\n\n**Method**\n\nThe interior angles form an arithmetic sequence:\n\n\\[\n177,\\ 175,\\ 173,\\ 171,\\ 169,\\ldots\n\\]\n\nSo\n\n\\[\na=177,\\quad d=-2\n\\]\n\nFor an \\(n\\)-sided polygon, the sum of the interior angles is\n\n\\[\n180(n-2)\n\\]\n\nThe sum of the arithmetic sequence is\n\n\\[\n\\frac{n}{2}\\left(2(177)+(n-1)(-2)\\right)\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=\\frac{n}{2}(354-2n+2)\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=\\frac{n}{2}(356-2n)\n\\]\n\n\\[\n=n(178-n)\n\\]\n\nSet this equal to the polygon angle sum:\n\n\\[\nn(178-n)=180(n-2)\n\\]\n\n\\[\n178n-n^2=180n-360\n\\]\n\n\\[\nn^2+2n-360=0\n\\]\n\nFactorise:\n\n\\[\n(n+20)(n-18)=0\n\\]\n\nSince \\(n>5\\),\n\n\\[\nn=18\n\\]\n\n**Answer:** \\(n=18\\)",
