    "source": "**Topic check:** Corrected from Ratio Toolkit to Vectors.\n\n**Method**\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OA}=4a,\\quad \\overrightarrow{OB}=6b,\\quad \\overrightarrow{AP}=2a+8b\n\\]\n\nSo\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OP}=\\overrightarrow{OA}+\\overrightarrow{AP}\n=4a+(2a+8b)=6a+8b\n\\]\n\nSince \\(Q\\) lies on \\(OP\\), let\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OQ}=\\lambda(6a+8b)\n\\]\n\nSince \\(Q\\) lies on \\(AB\\), let\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OQ}=\\overrightarrow{OA}+\\mu\\overrightarrow{AB}\n\\]\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{AB}=6b-4a\n\\]\n\nSo\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OQ}=4a+\\mu(6b-4a)=(4-4\\mu)a+6\\mu b\n\\]\n\nEquating coefficients:\n\n\\[\n6\\lambda=4-4\\mu,\\quad 8\\lambda=6\\mu\n\\]\n\nFrom \\(8\\lambda=6\\mu\\), \\(\\mu=\\frac43\\lambda\\).\n\n\\[\n6\\lambda=4-\\frac{16}{3}\\lambda\n\\]\n\n\\[\n34\\lambda=12,\\quad \\lambda=\\frac6{17}\n\\]\n\n\\[\n\\mu=\\frac{8}{17}\n\\]\n\nSo \\(AQ:QB=\\frac8{17}:\\frac9{17}\\).\n\n**Answer:** \\(AQ:QB=8:9\\)",
