    "source": "**Topic check:** Moved from Standard & Compound Units to Sine, Cosine Rule & Area of Triangles.\n\n**Method**\n\nFirst use triangle \\(ABD\\).\n\n\\[\nAB=9.4,\\quad AD=12.8,\\quad \\angle BAD=72^\\circ\n\\]\n\nUse the cosine rule to find \\(BD\\):\n\n\\[\nBD^2=9.4^2+12.8^2-2(9.4)(12.8)\\cos72^\\circ\n\\]\n\n\\[\nBD=13.3356\\ldots\n\\]\n\nIn triangle \\(BCD\\),\n\n\\[\n\\angle BDC=39^\\circ,\\quad \\angle BCD=54^\\circ\n\\]\n\nUse the sine rule:\n\n\\[\n\\frac{BC}{\\sin39^\\circ}=\\frac{BD}{\\sin54^\\circ}\n\\]\n\n\\[\nBC=\\frac{13.3356\\ldots\\sin39^\\circ}{\\sin54^\\circ}\n\\]\n\n\\[\nBC=10.3735\\ldots\n\\]\n\nCorrect to 3 significant figures,\n\n\\[\nBC=10.4\n\\]\n\n**Answer:** \\(10.4\\text{ cm}\\)",
