    "source": "**Topic check:** Correct.\n\n**Method**\n\n\\[\ny=kx^2+\\frac{16}{x}\n\\]\n\nDifferentiate:\n\n\\[\n\\frac{dy}{dx}=2kx-\\frac{16}{x^2}\n\\]\n\nAt the stationary point, \\(x=\\frac23\\), so the gradient is 0:\n\n\\[\n2k\\left(\\frac23\\right)-\\frac{16}{\\left(\\frac23\\right)^2}=0\n\\]\n\n\\[\n\\frac{4k}{3}-\\frac{16}{\\frac49}=0\n\\]\n\n\\[\n\\frac{4k}{3}-36=0\n\\]\n\n\\[\n\\frac{4k}{3}=36\n\\]\n\n\\[\nk=27\n\\]\n\nNow find \\(a\\), the \\(y\\)-coordinate when \\(x=\\frac23\\):\n\n\\[\na=27\\left(\\frac23\\right)^2+\\frac{16}{\\frac23}\n\\]\n\n\\[\na=27\\cdot\\frac49+24\n\\]\n\n\\[\na=12+24=36\n\\]\n\n**Answer:** \\(a=36\\)",
